      <focus/>
      <content>Cloud service models' forensics impact (IaaS: VM snapshots; PaaS: API logs; SaaS: provider-dependent). Shared responsibility model (customer vs. provider). NIST frameworks: SP 800-201 (CCFRA: actors like forensic investigator/provider; activities: planning/acquisition). NISTIR 8006: Addresses challenges (jurisdiction, volatility, anti-forensics) via reference architecture. Concept Map branches: 'Challenges (Multi-tenancy, Jurisdiction)' → 'NIST Frameworks'. Quiz: Diagram shared responsibility.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="3" name="Layer 3">
      <focus/>
      <content>Steps: Forensic readiness (proactive logging), acquisition (e.g., live forensics, API pulls), analysis (timeline reconstruction), reporting. Tools: CloudTrail, Azure Monitor, Volatility for memory. NIST CC FRA methodology: Preparation → Collection → Examination. Examples: IaaS snapshotting. Quiz: Sequence investigation steps.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="4" name="Layer 4">
      <focus/>
      <content>Link to incident response (NIST SP 800-61), legal/compliance (e.g., GDPR chain-of-custody, CLOUD Act jurisdiction). Advanced: Hybrid forensics, ML for anomaly detection. Concept Map: 'Integration' → 'Incident Response' ↔ 'Compliance' ↔ 'Tools'. Capstone: Design exercise.</content>
    </layer>
